{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":340,"text":"So, I have a strange career."},{"time":2405,"text":"I know it because people come up to me,\nlike colleagues, and say,"},{"time":5545,"text":"\"Chris, you have a strange career.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":7435,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":9102,"text":"And I can see their point,"},{"time":10445,"text":"because I started my career\nas a theoretical nuclear physicist."},{"time":15000,"text":"And I was thinking about quarks\nand gluons and heavy ion collisions,"},{"time":19188,"text":"and I was only 14 years old --"},{"time":21593,"text":"No, no, I wasn't 14 years old."},{"time":25237,"text":"But after that,"},{"time":27796,"text":"I actually had my own lab"},{"time":29761,"text":"in the Computational\nNeuroscience department,"},{"time":31900,"text":"and I wasn't doing any neuroscience."},{"time":33652,"text":"Later, I would work\non evolutionary genetics,"},{"time":36608,"text":"and I would work on systems biology."}]},{"cues":[{"time":38582,"text":"But I'm going to tell you\nabout something else today."},{"time":41271,"text":"I'm going to tell you\nabout how I learned something about life."},{"time":45557,"text":"And I was actually a rocket scientist."},{"time":49062,"text":"I wasn't really a rocket scientist,"},{"time":51389,"text":"but I was working\nat the Jet Propulsion Laboratory"},{"time":55769,"text":"in sunny California, where it's warm;"},{"time":58428,"text":"whereas now I am\nin the mid-West, and it's cold."},{"time":62300,"text":"But it was an exciting experience."},{"time":65000,"text":"One day, a NASA manager\ncomes into my office,"},{"time":68467,"text":"sits down and says,"},{"time":71602,"text":"\"Can you please tell us,\nhow do we look for life outside Earth?\""},{"time":76361,"text":"And that came as a surprise to me,"},{"time":78063,"text":"because I was actually hired\nto work on quantum computation."},{"time":82213,"text":"Yet, I had a very good answer."},{"time":83738,"text":"I said, \"I have no idea.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":85539,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":86713,"text":"And he told me, \"Biosignatures,\nwe need to look for a biosignature.\""},{"time":92079,"text":"And I said, \"What is that?\""},{"time":93467,"text":"And he said, \"It's any\nmeasurable phenomenon"},{"time":96088,"text":"that allows us to indicate\nthe presence of life.\""},{"time":99528,"text":"And I said, \"Really?"},{"time":101173,"text":"Because isn't that easy?"},{"time":103144,"text":"I mean, we have life."},{"time":104999,"text":"Can't you apply a definition,"},{"time":106995,"text":"for example, a Supreme Court-like\ndefinition of life?\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":111931,"text":"And then I thought about it\na little bit, and I said,"},{"time":114497,"text":"\"Well, is it really that easy?"},{"time":115996,"text":"Because, yes, if you see\nsomething like this,"},{"time":118213,"text":"then all right, fine,\nI'm going to call it life --"},{"time":120581,"text":"no doubt about it."},{"time":122257,"text":"But here's something.\""},{"time":123921,"text":"And he goes, \"Right,\nthat's life too. I know that.\""},{"time":127000,"text":"Except, if you think that life\nis also defined by things that die,"},{"time":131616,"text":"you're not in luck with this thing,"},{"time":133393,"text":"because that's actually\na very strange organism."},{"time":135679,"text":"It grows up into the adult stage like that"},{"time":137750,"text":"and then goes through\na Benjamin Button phase,"},{"time":140000,"text":"and actually goes backwards and backwards\nuntil it's like a little embryo again,"},{"time":144959,"text":"and then actually grows back up,\nand back down and back up --"},{"time":147897,"text":"sort of yo-yo -- and it never dies."},{"time":149700,"text":"So it's actually life,"},{"time":151950,"text":"but it's actually not\nas we thought life would be."},{"time":156491,"text":"And then you see something like that."},{"time":158426,"text":"And he was like, \"My God,\nwhat kind of a life form is that?\""},{"time":161323,"text":"Anyone know?"},{"time":162766,"text":"It's actually not life, it's a crystal."}]},{"cues":[{"time":166282,"text":"So once you start looking and looking\nat smaller and smaller things --"},{"time":169607,"text":"so this particular person wrote\na whole article and said,"},{"time":172793,"text":"\"Hey, these are bacteria.\""},{"time":174298,"text":"Except, if you look a little bit closer,"},{"time":176293,"text":"you see, in fact, that this thing\nis way too small to be anything like that."},{"time":179953,"text":"So he was convinced,\nbut, in fact, most people aren't."},{"time":183792,"text":"And then, of course,\nNASA also had a big announcement,"},{"time":187000,"text":"and President Clinton\ngave a press conference,"},{"time":189889,"text":"about this amazing discovery\nof life in a Martian meteorite."},{"time":195400,"text":"Except that nowadays,\nit's heavily disputed."},{"time":198806,"text":"If you take the lesson\nof all these pictures,"},{"time":201265,"text":"then you realize, well, actually,\nmaybe it's not that easy."},{"time":204183,"text":"Maybe I do need a definition of life"},{"time":207606,"text":"in order to make that kind of distinction."}]},{"cues":[{"time":209908,"text":"So can life be defined?"},{"time":212463,"text":"Well how would you go about it?"},{"time":213994,"text":"Well of course, you'd go\nto Encyclopedia Britannica and open at L."},{"time":218025,"text":"No, of course you don't do that;\nyou put it somewhere in Google."},{"time":221061,"text":"And then you might get something."}]},{"cues":[{"time":222676,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":223724,"text":"And what you might get --"},{"time":224966,"text":"and anything that actually refers\nto things that we are used to,"},{"time":228769,"text":"you throw away."},{"time":230015,"text":"And then you might come up\nwith something like this."},{"time":232537,"text":"And it says something complicated\nwith lots and lots of concepts."},{"time":235818,"text":"Who on Earth would write something\nas convoluted and complex and inane?"},{"time":242952,"text":"Oh, it's actually a really, really,\nimportant set of concepts."},{"time":246877,"text":"So I'm highlighting just a few words"},{"time":249000,"text":"and saying definitions\nlike that rely on things"},{"time":252948,"text":"that are not based on amino acids\nor leaves or anything that we are used to,"},{"time":259121,"text":"but in fact on processes only."},{"time":260896,"text":"And if you take a look at that,"},{"time":262791,"text":"this was actually in a book that I wrote\nthat deals with artificial life."},{"time":266272,"text":"And that explains why that NASA manager\nwas actually in my office to begin with."},{"time":270523,"text":"Because the idea was that,\nwith concepts like that,"},{"time":273634,"text":"maybe we can actually\nmanufacture a form of life."}]},{"cues":[{"time":277678,"text":"And so if you go and ask yourself,\n\"What on Earth is artificial life?\","},{"time":282499,"text":"let me give you a whirlwind tour\nof how all this stuff came about."},{"time":286192,"text":"And it started out quite a while ago,"},{"time":289351,"text":"when someone wrote one of the first\nsuccessful computer viruses."},{"time":293985,"text":"And for those of you\nwho aren't old enough,"},{"time":296182,"text":"you have no idea\nhow this infection was working --"},{"time":298789,"text":"namely, through these floppy disks."},{"time":301073,"text":"But the interesting thing\nabout these computer virus infections"},{"time":304984,"text":"was that, if you look at the rate\nat which the infection worked,"},{"time":308460,"text":"they show this spiky behavior\nthat you're used to from a flu virus."},{"time":312634,"text":"And it is in fact due to this arms race"},{"time":315000,"text":"between hackers\nand operating system designers"},{"time":318480,"text":"that things go back and forth."},{"time":320104,"text":"And the result is kind of\na tree of life of these viruses,"},{"time":324639,"text":"a phylogeny that looks very much\nlike the type of life"},{"time":328268,"text":"that we're used to,\nat least on the viral level."}]},{"cues":[{"time":330721,"text":"So is that life?"},{"time":332266,"text":"Not as far as I'm concerned."},{"time":333906,"text":"Why? Because these things\ndon't evolve by themselves."},{"time":336772,"text":"In fact, they have hackers writing them."},{"time":338749,"text":"But the idea was taken\nvery quickly a little bit further,"},{"time":342103,"text":"when a scientist working\nat the Santa Fe Institute decided,"},{"time":345438,"text":"\"Why don't we try to package\nthese little viruses"},{"time":348595,"text":"in artificial worlds\ninside of the computer"},{"time":350834,"text":"and let them evolve?\""},{"time":352129,"text":"And this was Steen Rasmussen."},{"time":353747,"text":"And he designed this system,\nbut it really didn't work,"},{"time":356463,"text":"because his viruses\nwere constantly destroying each other."},{"time":359371,"text":"But there was another scientist\nwho had been watching this, an ecologist."},{"time":362912,"text":"And he went home and says,\n\"I know how to fix this.\""},{"time":365428,"text":"And he wrote the Tierra system,"},{"time":367096,"text":"and, in my book,"},{"time":368325,"text":"is in fact one of the first\ntruly artificial living systems --"},{"time":372173,"text":"except for the fact that these programs\ndidn't really grow in complexity."}]},{"cues":[{"time":375659,"text":"So having seen this work,\nworked a little bit on this,"},{"time":378547,"text":"this is where I came in."},{"time":380229,"text":"And I decided to create a system\nthat has all the properties"},{"time":383896,"text":"that are necessary to see, in fact,\nthe evolution of complexity,"},{"time":387766,"text":"more and more complex\nproblems constantly evolving."},{"time":391092,"text":"And of course, since I really don't know\nhow to write code, I had help in this."},{"time":394900,"text":"I had two undergraduate students"},{"time":396472,"text":"at California Institute of Technology\nthat worked with me."},{"time":399225,"text":"That's Charles Ofria on the left,\nTitus Brown on the right."},{"time":402101,"text":"They are now, actually,\nrespectable professors"},{"time":404460,"text":"at Michigan State University,"},{"time":406226,"text":"but I can assure you, back in the day,\nwe were not a respectable team."},{"time":410751,"text":"And I'm really happy\nthat no photo survives"},{"time":412824,"text":"of the three of us\nanywhere close together."}]},{"cues":[{"time":416092,"text":"But what is this system like?"},{"time":417991,"text":"Well I can't really go into the details,"},{"time":420204,"text":"but what you see here\nis some of the entrails."},{"time":422881,"text":"But what I wanted to focus on\nis this type of population structure."},{"time":426990,"text":"There's about 10,000\nprograms sitting here."},{"time":429486,"text":"And all different strains\nare colored in different colors."},{"time":432429,"text":"And as you see here, there are groups\nthat are growing on top of each other,"},{"time":436057,"text":"because they are spreading."},{"time":437422,"text":"Any time there is a program\nthat's better at surviving in this world,"},{"time":441550,"text":"due to whatever mutation it has acquired,"},{"time":443542,"text":"it is going to spread over the others\nand drive the others to extinction."}]},{"cues":[{"time":447036,"text":"So I'm going to show you a movie"},{"time":448615,"text":"where you're going to see\nthat kind of dynamic."},{"time":450866,"text":"And these kinds of experiments are started\nwith programs that we wrote ourselves."},{"time":455166,"text":"We write our own stuff, replicate it,\nand are very proud of ourselves."},{"time":458527,"text":"And we put them in,\nand what you see immediately"},{"time":461327,"text":"is that there are waves\nand waves of innovation."},{"time":464417,"text":"By the way, this is highly accelerated,"},{"time":466335,"text":"so it's like a 1000 generations a second."},{"time":468556,"text":"But immediately, the system goes like,\n\"What kind of dumb piece of code was this?"},{"time":472547,"text":"This can be improved upon\nin so many ways, so quickly.\""},{"time":476292,"text":"So you see waves of new types\ntaking over the other types."},{"time":480064,"text":"And this type of activity\ngoes on for quite a while,"},{"time":482650,"text":"until the main easy things\nhave been acquired by these programs."},{"time":487495,"text":"And then, you see\nsort of like a stasis coming on"},{"time":491000,"text":"where the system essentially waits"},{"time":493000,"text":"for a new type of innovation,\nlike this one,"},{"time":496207,"text":"which is going to spread over\nall the other innovations that were before"},{"time":500513,"text":"and is erasing the genes\nthat it had before,"},{"time":503000,"text":"until a new type of higher level\nof complexity has been achieved."},{"time":507000,"text":"And this process goes on and on and on."}]},{"cues":[{"time":510467,"text":"So what we see here"},{"time":511806,"text":"is a system that lives in very much\nthe way we're used to how life goes."},{"time":516688,"text":"But what the NASA people\nhad asked me really was,"},{"time":521213,"text":"\"Do these guys have a biosignature?"},{"time":524580,"text":"Can we measure this type of life?"},{"time":526417,"text":"Because if we can,"},{"time":527633,"text":"maybe we have a chance of actually\ndiscovering life somewhere else"},{"time":531506,"text":"without being biased\nby things like amino acids.\""},{"time":535221,"text":"So I said, \"Well, perhaps\nwe should construct a biosignature"},{"time":539778,"text":"based on life as a universal process."},{"time":543000,"text":"In fact, it should perhaps make use\nof the concepts that I developed"},{"time":547888,"text":"just in order to sort of capture\nwhat a simple living system might be.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":551999,"text":"And the thing I came up with --"},{"time":553542,"text":"I have to first give you\nan introduction about the idea,"},{"time":557548,"text":"and maybe that would be\na meaning detector,"},{"time":561111,"text":"rather than a life detector."},{"time":563226,"text":"And the way we would do that --"},{"time":565000,"text":"I would like to find out\nhow I can distinguish text"},{"time":567660,"text":"that was written by a million monkeys,\nas opposed to text that is in our books."},{"time":572645,"text":"And I would like to do it in such a way"},{"time":574546,"text":"that I don't actually have to be able\nto read the language,"},{"time":577448,"text":"because I'm sure I won't be able to."},{"time":579242,"text":"As long as I know\nthat there's some sort of alphabet."},{"time":581766,"text":"So here would be a frequency plot"},{"time":584120,"text":"of how often you find\neach of the 26 letters of the alphabet"},{"time":587526,"text":"in a text written by random monkeys."},{"time":590195,"text":"And obviously, each of these letters\ncomes off about roughly equally frequent."}]},{"cues":[{"time":594773,"text":"But if you now look at the same\ndistribution in English texts,"},{"time":598389,"text":"it looks like that."},{"time":600202,"text":"And I'm telling you,\nthis is very robust across English texts."},{"time":603774,"text":"And if I look at French texts,\nit looks a little bit different,"},{"time":606782,"text":"or Italian or German."},{"time":607984,"text":"They all have their own type\nof frequency distribution,"},{"time":611424,"text":"but it's robust."},{"time":612881,"text":"It doesn't matter whether it writes\nabout politics or about science."},{"time":616112,"text":"It doesn't matter whether it's a poem\nor whether it's a mathematical text."},{"time":621916,"text":"It's a robust signature,"},{"time":623777,"text":"and it's very stable."},{"time":625621,"text":"As long as our books\nare written in English --"},{"time":627802,"text":"because people are rewriting them\nand recopying them --"},{"time":630617,"text":"it's going to be there."}]},{"cues":[{"time":632000,"text":"So that inspired me to think about,\nwell, what if I try to use this idea"},{"time":637785,"text":"in order, not to detect random texts\nfrom texts with meaning,"},{"time":641564,"text":"but rather detect the fact\nthat there is meaning"},{"time":645317,"text":"in the biomolecules that make up life."},{"time":647868,"text":"But first I have to ask:"},{"time":649060,"text":"what are these building blocks,"},{"time":650572,"text":"like the alphabet, elements\nthat I showed you?"},{"time":652892,"text":"Well it turns out, we have\nmany different alternatives"},{"time":655789,"text":"for such a set of building blocks."},{"time":658127,"text":"We could use amino acids,"},{"time":659399,"text":"we could use nucleic acids,\ncarboxylic acids, fatty acids."},{"time":662625,"text":"In fact, chemistry's extremely rich,\nand our body uses a lot of them."}]},{"cues":[{"time":666087,"text":"So that we actually, to test this idea,"},{"time":668417,"text":"first took a look at amino acids\nand some other carboxylic acids."},{"time":671988,"text":"And here's the result."},{"time":673483,"text":"Here is, in fact, what you get"},{"time":676673,"text":"if you, for example, look\nat the distribution of amino acids"},{"time":679720,"text":"on a comet or in interstellar space\nor, in fact, in a laboratory,"},{"time":684479,"text":"where you made very sure\nthat in your primordial soup,"},{"time":687162,"text":"there is no living stuff in there."},{"time":689104,"text":"What you find is mostly\nglycine and then alanine"},{"time":692007,"text":"and there's some trace elements\nof the other ones."},{"time":694390,"text":"That is also very robust --"},{"time":696843,"text":"what you find in systems like Earth"},{"time":700699,"text":"where there are amino acids,\nbut there is no life."}]},{"cues":[{"time":703868,"text":"But suppose you take some dirt\nand dig through it"},{"time":708522,"text":"and then put it into these spectrometers,"},{"time":711506,"text":"because there's bacteria\nall over the place;"},{"time":713628,"text":"or you take water anywhere on Earth,"},{"time":715883,"text":"because it's teaming with life,"},{"time":717424,"text":"and you make the same analysis;"},{"time":719198,"text":"the spectrum looks completely different."},{"time":721799,"text":"Of course, there is still\nglycine and alanine,"},{"time":725198,"text":"but in fact, there are these heavy\nelements, these heavy amino acids,"},{"time":728542,"text":"that are being produced\nbecause they are valuable to the organism."},{"time":733067,"text":"And some other ones\nthat are not used in the set of 20,"},{"time":737029,"text":"they will not appear at all\nin any type of concentration."},{"time":739951,"text":"So this also turns out\nto be extremely robust."},{"time":742680,"text":"It doesn't matter what kind of sediment\nyou're using to grind up,"},{"time":745822,"text":"whether it's bacteria\nor any other plants or animals."},{"time":749125,"text":"Anywhere there's life,"},{"time":750573,"text":"you're going to have this distribution,"},{"time":752548,"text":"as opposed to that distribution."},{"time":754389,"text":"And it is detectable\nnot just in amino acids."}]},{"cues":[{"time":757650,"text":"Now you could ask:"},{"time":758891,"text":"Well, what about these Avidians?"},{"time":762074,"text":"The Avidians being the denizens\nof this computer world"},{"time":765149,"text":"where they are perfectly happy\nreplicating and growing in complexity."},{"time":768618,"text":"So this is the distribution that you get\nif, in fact, there is no life."},{"time":773659,"text":"They have about 28 of these instructions."},{"time":776401,"text":"And if you have a system where\nthey're being replaced one by the other,"},{"time":779777,"text":"it's like the monkeys\nwriting on a typewriter."},{"time":781986,"text":"Each of these instructions\nappears with roughly the equal frequency."},{"time":787115,"text":"But if you now take\na set of replicating guys"},{"time":791919,"text":"like in the video that you saw,"},{"time":793893,"text":"it looks like this."},{"time":796199,"text":"So there are some instructions"},{"time":797696,"text":"that are extremely valuable\nto these organisms,"},{"time":800153,"text":"and their frequency is going to be high."},{"time":802147,"text":"And there's actually some instructions\nthat you only use once, if ever."},{"time":806212,"text":"So they are either poisonous"},{"time":807759,"text":"or really should be used\nat less of a level than random."},{"time":812288,"text":"In this case, the frequency is lower."},{"time":815932,"text":"And so now we can see,\nis that really a robust signature?"},{"time":818627,"text":"I can tell you indeed it is,"},{"time":820008,"text":"because this type of spectrum,\njust like what you've seen in books,"},{"time":823280,"text":"and just like what you've seen\nin amino acids,"},{"time":825457,"text":"it doesn't really matter\nhow you change the environment,"},{"time":828123,"text":"it's very robust, it's going\nto reflect the environment."}]},{"cues":[{"time":830771,"text":"So I'm going to show you now\na little experiment that we did."},{"time":833744,"text":"And I have to explain to you,"},{"time":835152,"text":"the top of this graph"},{"time":836358,"text":"shows you that frequency\ndistribution that I talked about."},{"time":839126,"text":"Here, that's the lifeless environment"},{"time":842957,"text":"where each instruction occurs\nat an equal frequency."},{"time":847304,"text":"And below there, I show, in fact,\nthe mutation rate in the environment."},{"time":852321,"text":"And I'm starting this\nat a mutation rate that is so high"},{"time":855648,"text":"that even if you would drop\na replicating program"},{"time":859638,"text":"that would otherwise happily grow up\nto fill the entire world,"},{"time":863787,"text":"if you drop it in, it gets mutated\nto death immediately."},{"time":866821,"text":"So there is no life possible\nat that type of mutation rate."},{"time":872191,"text":"But then I'm going to slowly\nturn down the heat, so to speak,"},{"time":876251,"text":"and then there's this viability threshold"},{"time":878460,"text":"where now it would be possible\nfor a replicator to actually live."},{"time":882376,"text":"And indeed, we're going to be dropping\nthese guys into that soup all the time."}]},{"cues":[{"time":888159,"text":"So let's see what that looks like."},{"time":889819,"text":"So first, nothing, nothing, nothing."},{"time":892841,"text":"Too hot, too hot."},{"time":894680,"text":"Now the viability threshold is reached,"},{"time":897000,"text":"and the frequency distribution\nhas dramatically changed"},{"time":901516,"text":"and, in fact, stabilizes."},{"time":903016,"text":"And now what I did there"},{"time":904550,"text":"is, I was being nasty,\nI just turned up the heat again and again."},{"time":908172,"text":"And of course, it reaches\nthe viability threshold."},{"time":910542,"text":"And I'm just showing this to you\nagain because it's so nice."},{"time":913434,"text":"You hit the viability threshold."},{"time":915000,"text":"The distribution changes to \"alive!\""},{"time":917431,"text":"And then, once you hit the threshold"},{"time":920672,"text":"where the mutation rate is so high\nthat you cannot self-reproduce,"},{"time":924745,"text":"you cannot copy the information\nforward to your offspring"},{"time":929690,"text":"without making so many mistakes\nthat your ability to replicate vanishes."},{"time":934444,"text":"And then, that signature is lost."}]},{"cues":[{"time":937956,"text":"What do we learn from that?"},{"time":939686,"text":"Well, I think we learn\na number of things from that."},{"time":943506,"text":"One of them is,"},{"time":945000,"text":"if we are able to think about life\nin abstract terms --"},{"time":950248,"text":"and we're not talking\nabout things like plants,"},{"time":952903,"text":"and we're not talking about amino acids,"},{"time":954852,"text":"and we're not talking about bacteria,"},{"time":956640,"text":"but we think in terms of processes --"},{"time":958774,"text":"then we could start to think about life"},{"time":961000,"text":"not as something\nthat is so special to Earth,"},{"time":963643,"text":"but that, in fact, could exist anywhere."},{"time":966177,"text":"Because it really only has to do\nwith these concepts of information,"},{"time":970514,"text":"of storing information\nwithin physical substrates --"},{"time":974596,"text":"anything: bits, nucleic acids,\nanything that's an alphabet --"},{"time":978636,"text":"and make sure that there's some process"},{"time":980539,"text":"so that this information can be stored\nfor much longer than you would expect --"},{"time":984816,"text":"the time scales for\nthe deterioration of information."},{"time":989176,"text":"And if you can do that,\nthen you have life."}]},{"cues":[{"time":992368,"text":"So the first thing that we learn"},{"time":994646,"text":"is that it is possible to define life\nin terms of processes alone,"},{"time":999882,"text":"without referring at all\nto the type of things that we hold dear,"},{"time":1004883,"text":"as far as the type of life on Earth is."},{"time":1007578,"text":"And that, in a sense, removes us again,"},{"time":1010243,"text":"like all of our scientific discoveries,\nor many of them --"},{"time":1013098,"text":"it's this continuous dethroning of man --"},{"time":1015893,"text":"of how we think we're special\nbecause we're alive."},{"time":1018644,"text":"Well, we can make life;\nwe can make life in the computer."},{"time":1021724,"text":"Granted, it's limited,"},{"time":1023565,"text":"but we have learned what it takes\nin order to actually construct it."},{"time":1028706,"text":"And once we have that,"},{"time":1031518,"text":"then it is not such\na difficult task anymore"},{"time":1034189,"text":"to say, if we understand\nthe fundamental processes"},{"time":1038365,"text":"that do not refer\nto any particular substrate,"},{"time":1041731,"text":"then we can go out and try other worlds,"},{"time":1045523,"text":"figure out what kind of chemical\nalphabets might there be,"},{"time":1050033,"text":"figure enough about the normal chemistry,\nthe geochemistry of the planet,"},{"time":1054782,"text":"so that we know what this distribution\nwould look like in the absence of life,"},{"time":1058580,"text":"and then look for large\ndeviations from this --"},{"time":1061575,"text":"this thing sticking out, which says,\n\"This chemical really shouldn't be there.\""},{"time":1066711,"text":"Now we don't know that there's life then,"},{"time":1068690,"text":"but we could say,"},{"time":1069921,"text":"\"Well at least I'm going to have to take\na look very precisely at this chemical"},{"time":1073714,"text":"and see where it comes from.\""},{"time":1075783,"text":"And that might be our chance\nof actually discovering life"},{"time":1079518,"text":"when we cannot visibly see it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1081661,"text":"And so that's really the only\ntake-home message that I have for you."},{"time":1086249,"text":"Life can be less mysterious\nthan we make it out to be"},{"time":1090504,"text":"when we try to think\nabout how it would be on other planets."},{"time":1094280,"text":"And if we remove the mystery of life,"},{"time":1097691,"text":"then I think it is a little bit easier\nfor us to think about how we live,"},{"time":1102400,"text":"and how perhaps we're not as special\nas we always think we are."},{"time":1105482,"text":"And I'm going to leave you with that."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1107752,"text":"And thank you very much."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1109000,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}